<DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
   <title> The animation-direction Property </title>
   <style type="text/css">
      @keyframes myAnimation {
         from {
            background-color: gold;
            left: 0px;
         }
         to {
            background-color: green;
            left: 200px;
         }
      }
      div {
         animation-name: myAnimation;
         animation-duration: 2s;
         animation-iteration-count: infinite;
         animation-direction: normal;
         position: relative;
         width: 100px;
         height: 100px;
      }
   </style>
</head>
<body>
   <p> We have defined the <b>animation-iteration-count</b> CSS property to see how <b>animation-direction</b> property works. </p>
   <div></div>
</body>
</html>